.TH ABORT 2
.SH NAME
abort \- generate a fault
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include <u.h>
.br
.B #include <libc.h>
.PP
.nf
.B
void	abort(void)
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Abort
prints the caller address to standard error and causes an access fault, 
so that the current process will enter the `Broken' state.
The process can then be inspected by a debugger.
.SH SOURCE
.B /sys/src/libc/9sys/abort.c
